        <h2 style="text-align: center;">You Are: </h2>
        <h1 style="text-align: center; font-size:50px; color: #c41e3a">UNDERWEIGHT </h1>
        <br>

        <div class="text">
            <t>Being underweight can represent as many health concerns to an individual as
                being overweight can. If a person is underweight, their body may not be getting the nutrients it needs
                to build healthy bones, skin, and hair.

                While some people may have a genetic background or a medical illness that prevents them from putting on
                weight, there are interventions doctors can recommend to help a person gain weight.</t>
            <br>
            <br>
            <t>
                There’s a lot of focus in the medical world on the health effects of being overweight, but what about
                the effects of being underweight? There are certain health risks associated with being underweight or
                having poor nutrition.
                <BR>
                <BR>
                These risks include:
                <ul class="a">
                    <li>Malnutrition, vitamin deficiencies, or anemia</li>
                    <li>Osteoporosis from too little vitamin D and calcium</li>
                    <li>Decreased immune function</li>
                    <li>Increased risk for complications from surgery</li>
                    <li>Fertility issues caused by irregular menstrual cycles</li>
                    <li>Growth and development issues, especially in children and teenagers</li>
                </ul>

            </t>
            <br>
            <br>
            <BR>

            <h2> PREVENTIVE MEASURES: </h2>
            <BR>

            <div class="image">
                <div class="header">
                    <img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTjTEiDUQnrXUR63KB09O1TcNwDcbQHMhOANA&usqp=CAU"
