                    <h1>&nbsp;AVOID SMOKING AND DRINKING</h1>
                    <T style="color:grey">&nbsp; Many people gain weight when they quit smoking cigarettes. On average,
                        people gain 5 to 10
                        pounds
                        (2.25 to &nbsp;&nbsp;4.5 kilograms) in the months after they
                        give up smoking. You may put off
                        quitting if
                        you are worried about &nbsp;&nbsp;adding extra weight. But not smoking is
                        one of
                        the best
                        things you can do
                        for your health.</T>
                </div>
            </div>
            <br> <br> <br>
